   Visiting Ames
   Planning a trip to the area and want to see what NASA Ames has to
   offer? Look here for information on directions to the center, a map of
   the center, obtaining a visitors badge or signing up for a tour.

   (As of June 2000, tours will no longer be offered until further notice
   ).
   There are many places at Ames that are open to the public. Check out
   the Moffett Museum, the Visitor Center and gift shop , the Educator
   Resource Center, the California Air and Space Center and the Teacher
   Institute.

   About NASA Ames

                  Directions and Badging

                                        Tours and Destinations

   About NASA Ames
   NASA Ames Research Center is one of the twelve NASA centers located
   throughout the U.S. Ames Research Center is located at the southern end
   of San Francisco Bay in the heart of the Silicon Valley at the
   Moffett Federal Airfield.
   Ames is a world-class research facility that provides vital information
   and technology for the United States aerospace program. Ames has two
   primary missions: Astrobiology and Aviation Operations. Ames is also
   NASAs Center of Excellence for Information Technology. NASA Ames Home
   Page
   [USEMAP:NASA%20Field%20Centers.gif]
   Directions and Badging
   [USEMAP:Map%20of%20Bay.gif]
   Location:
       NASA Ames is located at Moffett Field Airfield, which borders the
       cities of Mountain View and Sunnyvale.

   Directions:
   From San Francisco International Airport (SFO) travel South US 101 and
       exit at Moffett Field.
       From San Jose Airport (SJC) travel North US 101 and exit at Moffett
       Field.

   Bay area Map and Map of Ames facilities
   Badging:
       All visitors are welcome to the Ames Education Resource Center or
       the Ames Visitor Center. Guests do not need a badge to enter these
       facilities.
       For access inside Ames Research Center or Moffett Field, visitors
       should go to the Visitor Badging Office, located at the Moffett
       Field Main Gate, to get a badge. An Ames or Moffett Employee must
       sponsor any visit inside the Center.

   Tours and Destinations
   Educator Resource Center (ERC) provides educators with NASA related
   instructional materials suitable for use in the classroom. Much of the
   material is free; videotapes and slides may be copied. Resources
   include: curriculum materials, classroom activities, Internet access,
   lesson plans, computer programs, videos, 35 mm slides and publications.
   Contact: ERC (650) 504-3574
   The Moffett Museum --The Moffett Field Historical Society was founded
   in May of 1993, as the result of the community "Hail and Farewell" for
   the Navy as Moffett Field was closing. One year later the Moffett Field
   museum was created. The museum, managed and staffed by volunteers, is
   located in the West side of historic "Hangar One".
   Tours of Ames Be sure to plan ahead when planning a tour of Ames. Visit
   this site for information on how to make a reservation.

   (As of June 2000, tours will no longer be offered until further notice
   ).

   Visitor Center/Gift Shop The visitor center offers exhibits related to
   NASAs exciting programs and missions, and no visit is complete without
   a souvenir from the gift shop.
   Future Destinations
   California Air and Space Center (CASC) Learn more about this future
   educational and entertainment facility, which will reside in historic
   Hangar 1. The CASC will showcase Americas achievements in aeronautics
   and space and will support NASAs mission at the Ames Research Complex
   while heightening public awareness of the importance of science and
   technology to our future.
   Teacher Institute The California Air and Space Center Teacher Institute
   will provide professional development opportunities for K-12 teachers
   of science, mathematics and technology. The Institute will include the
   NASA Academy, which will team the knowledge of NASA scientists and
   engineers with the pedagogical knowledge of master teachers to provide
   interdisciplinary, laboratory-based professional development courses.
   It will also feature NASA Curriculum Online which will bring the
   exciting story of NASA research projects to teachers as these stories
   unfold.

